Table_1_variables <- rawSelection2 |>
  select(gender,ethnicity) |>
  mutate(
    ethnicity = recode_factor(ethnicity,
      "Irish White" = "Irish White",
      "Northern Irish/English/Welsh/Scotish" = "Northern Irish/English/Welsh/Scotish",
      .default = "Other"
    )
  ) |>
  group_by(gender, ethnicity) |>
  reframe(n = n())  |>
  group_by(gender) |>
  mutate(percentage = n/sum(n)*100)

sumCutOff <- function(value, n, cutoff){
  sum(n[value >= cutoff & value < 90])
}

          cutoff_4=sumCutOff(value, n, 4)/sum(n)*100,

uniqueCutOff <- function(value, subject, cutoff){
  length(
    unique(
      subject[value >= cutoff & value < 90]
    )
  )
}

    pivot_longer(

    values_to = "score"
  ) |>
  mutate(
    sextant = str_replace(sextant, "BPE_", ""),
    score = as.factor(score),
    participant_id = as.numeric(as.factor(participant_id))
  )

  geom_tile() +

 ggtitle("BPE Score")

bpeTable <- rawSelection2 %>% 
  select(starts_with("BPE_"), "participant_id", gender) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(participant_id)) %>%
    pivot_longer(
    cols = starts_with("BPE_"),
    names_to = "sextant",
    values_to = "score"
  ) |>
  filter(score != 'X = sextant excluded')  |> 
  group_by(
    participant_id, gender
  ) |>
  reframe(
    score = max(score)
  ) |>
  mutate(
    participant_id = as.numeric(as.factor(participant_id))
  ) |>
  group_by(gender, score) |>
  reframe(countSubject = n_distinct(participant_id)
          ) |>
  group_by(gender) |>
  mutate(pcSubject = countSubject / sum(countSubject)* 100
         )
